				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Adding 16 bit numbers is pretty straight forward. The only difference between adding a 16 bit number and two 8 bit numbers is you don't clear the carry between bytes.<br /><br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">num1: .res 2<br />num2: .res 2<br />result: .res 2<br /><br />clc<br />lda num1+0<br />adc num2+0<br />sta result+0<br />lda num1+1<br />adc num2+1<br />sta result+1</div></div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

						<table width="100%" cellspacing="0">
						<tr valign="middle">
							<td class="gensmall" align="right">
							
							</td>
						</tr>
						</table>
					</td>
				</tr>
				</table>
			</td>
